tern
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a seabird related to the gull, having a slender body, long wings, and graceful flight.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: check white-fronted, black-fronted, Antarctic, caspian; sea-swallow, tara, kahawai-bird
Citations
Date:  25/3/1773
Source:  Resolution Journal of J.R. Forster, The
Author:  FORSTER
Vol / Page:  2/237
Edition:
Quote:   Saw common Albatrosses, ... & some affirmed to have seen Eggbirds or Terns. [ed. fn] Not specifically identifiable but perhaps the White-fronted Tern <i>Sterna striata</i> (Gmelin, 1789). <i>Ibid.</i> 2/289 <i>Capt Furneaux </i>dined with us & I described a new <i>Owl</i> & a new <i>Tern</i>, the former of which was drawn by George. [ed. fn] <i>Sterna antarctica</i> of <i>Descr. Anim</i>., p.107. Now the Black-fronted Tern <i>Chlidonias hybrida albostriatus</i> (Gray, 1845).
